<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>hello, dears.</p> <p>I&#39;m on a quest. I&#39;ve been travelling for a while. And I might be closing on its end, I feel. With Emacs.</p> <p>I have MIDI devices connected to a Macbook. I need Emacs to listen to their MIDI events and insert as text. Simple. Just letters or numbers.</p> <p>Google has brought me to these ways:</p> <p>- <a href="https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/EmacsMidi">emacswiki</a>, <a href="https://github.com/jnykopp/emaccordion">emaccordion</a>, <a href="https://github.com/andreasjansson/midimacs">midimacs</a>, <a href="https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/midi-kbd.html">midi-kbd</a> : based on ALSA (linux), unavailable in Mac OS X.</p> <p>- <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/elisp/Serial-Ports.html">(make-serial-port)</a> : MIDI devices are generally USB, not serial.</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>Could someone point me in the right direction?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/lets-start-reading"> /u/lets-start-reading </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/scao7x/emacs_midi_input/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/scao7x/emacs_midi_input/">[comments]</a></span>